        "text": "The maximum number of hard links to a single file is limited by the size of the reference counter. On Unix-like systems the counter is usually machine-word-sized (32- or 64-bit: 4,294,967,295 or 18,446,744,073,709,551,615 links, respectively), though in some filesystems, such as [[Btrfs]], the number of hard links is limited more strictly by their on-disk format. As of [[Linux]] 3.11, the [[ext4]] filesystem limits the number of hard links on a file to 65,000.[ ] [[Windows]] with [[NTFS]] filesystem has a limit of 1024 hard links on a file.[https://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/library/aa363860%28v=vs.85%29.aspx MSDN - CreateHardLink function]"
